<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's been enjoying some well-deserved downtime with her husband Cooke Maroney in lockdown.</p>

<p>And Jennifer Lawrence continued her break from her typically busy schedule as she and art dealer Cooke enjoyed a dinner date in New York City on Wednesday evening.</p>

<p>The actress, 30, caught the eye in monochrome pinstripe trousers as she and her man, 34, sported protective face masks amid the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>Quality time: Jennifer Lawrence continued her break from her typically busy schedule as she and her husband Cooke Maroney enjoyed a dinner date in New York City on Wednesday</p>

<p>Dressing down her look, the Red Sparrow star teamed her patterned bottoms with a plain white T-shirt and comfy trainers.</p>

<p>The media personality carried her essentials in a chain-strap handbag, while her tresses were worn loose.</p>

<p>Cooke, meanwhile, looked effortlessly cool in a designer T-shirt, baggy trousers and a dark jacket.</p>

<p>'He's just the best person I've ever met': The actress, 30, married the gallerist, 34, at the Belcourt of Newport in front of celebrity guests last October (pictured in 2018)</p>

<p>Jennifer married the gallerist at the Belcourt of Newport in Rhode Island in front of celebrity guests including Adele, Cameron Diaz and Emma Stone back in October 2019.</p>

<p>The Hunger Games star was linked to Cooke after they were introduced by mutual friends, and by last February, the blonde was spotted wearing an engagement ring.</p>

<p>'Well, he's just the best person I've ever met in my whole life. It was a very, very easy decision,' she told Entertainment Tonight after accepting his proposal. </p>

<p>'Jennifer and Cooke were at the weddings bureau together on the morning of September 16,' an insider previously said.</p>

<p>They added: 'They had a female friend and a photographer with them the entire time. They sat in the couches to the left and were trying to remain unseen.' </p>

<p>Last month, it was reported that the thespian made a colossal $5.7million loss on her sprawling New York City penthouse as it finally sold for $9.9million after a year on the market. </p>

<p>The Oscar-winning star slashed more than $3million off the original price of $15.6million in January, asking for offers of $12million.</p>

<p>Just the two of us: Since tying the knot, the couple have been maintaining a low profile (pictured in February)</p>
